-- Treger Earns $400 Million Brokering Western Coal Takeover Deal, FT Says
-- B y   N i d a a   B a k h s h
-- 2010-11-20T12:27:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-20/treger-earns-400-million-in-western-coal-takeover-ft-reports.html
Julian Treger  earned $400 million by
brokering a deal this week between Canadian mining company
Western Coal Corp. and U.S.-based Walter Energy Inc., the
 Financial Times  reported today.  Treger is managing director of the U.K.-based hedge fund
Audley Capital Advisors LLP.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nidaa Bakhsh in London at 
 nbakhsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
